## Problema 2 <a name="2"></a>
**Enunciado:**
Termistor NTC:
$$R_0 = 10000$$
$$\Omega$$
$$T_0 = 298$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$B = 3984$$
$$\text{K}$$
Calcular la
sensibilidad
$$S$$
y la
sensibilidad
unitaria
$$S_u$$
a:
$$25$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
$$50$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
y
$$75$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
.

**Solución:**
1. Fórmulas:
$$S(T) = -\frac{B}{T^2} \cdot R(T)$$
$$S_u(T) = -\frac{B}{T^2} \cdot 100$$
$$\%$$
$$\text{/K}$$

2. Valores de
resistencia:
-
$$T = 298$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$R = 10000$$
$$\Omega$$
-
$$T = 323$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$R = 3598.7$$
$$\Omega$$
-
$$T = 348$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$R = 1475.9$$
$$\Omega$$

3. Sensibilidad
- A
$$25$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
:
$$S = -\frac{3984}{298^2} \cdot 10000$$
$$S = -448.6$$
$$\Omega\text{/K}$$
- A
$$50$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
:
$$S = -\frac{3984}{323^2} \cdot 3598.7$$
$$S = -137.4$$
$$\Omega\text{/K}$$
- A
$$75$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
:
$$S = -\frac{3984}{348^2} \cdot 1475.9$$
$$S = -48.5$$
$$\Omega\text{/K}$$

4. Sensibilidad
Unitaria
- A
$$25$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
:
$$S_u = -\frac{3984}{298^2} \cdot 100$$
$$S_u = -4.48$$
$$\%\text{/K}$$
- A
$$50$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
:
$$S_u = -\frac{3984}{323^2} \cdot 100$$
$$S_u = -3.82$$
$$\%\text{/K}$$
- A
$$75$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
:
$$S_u = -\frac{3984}{348^2} \cdot 100$$
$$S_u = -2.29$$
$$\%\text{/K}$$

